        <abstract>
            <p>CD’s health and his father’s death have delayed his answer. Describes J. M. Gully’s water-cure.</p> 
<p>JDH’s Galapagos papers [<hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 20 (1851): 163–233] have excellent discussion of geographical distribution, but why no general treatment of affinities?</p> 
            <p>CD’s views on clay-slate laminae.</p>
            <p>Turmoil in Royal Society between naturalists and physicists.</p>
        </abstract>
